    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Movember]]></title>
    <link href="http://andrewdotni.ch//blog/2011/11/11/movember/"/>
    <updated>2011-11-11T11:23:00+11:00</updated>
    <id>http://andrewdotni.ch//blog/2011/11/11/movember</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<div class='post'>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="tr-caption-container" style="float: left; margin-right: 3em; text-align: left;"><tbody><tr><td style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-4iMF1g43lJ0/TrxvCDPwtrI/AAAAAAAAAE4/ucxAZOmgo9k/s1600/mo_before.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"><img border="0" height="200" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-4iMF1g43lJ0/TrxvCDPwtrI/AAAAAAAAAE4/ucxAZOmgo9k/s200/mo_before.jpg" width="150" /></a></td></tr><tr><td class="tr-caption" style="text-align: center;">Before</td></tr></tbody></table><div style="text-align: justify;">Anyone who knows me well would agree that changes to the amount and style of hair on my head are few and far between. Once I get into a habit, it tends not to change for some time. And then, suddenly, I'll decide it's time for something different and without warning, spring it on the world.</div><div style="text-align: justify;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: justify;">I may have just done that again.</div><div style="text-align: justify;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><div style="text-align: justify;">I've had a small <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Van_Dyke_beard">Van Dyck-style</a> beard for a few years, but I decided that I wanted to try something different. And what better time to do it than <a href="http://au.movember.com/">Movember</a>?</div></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="tr-caption-container" style="float: left; text-align: left; margin-right: 3em"><tbody><tr><td style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-9M2jmE-JKqE/TrxvEQRMFJI/AAAAAAAAAFA/3imu9FDUyLo/s1600/mo_after.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"><img border="0" height="200" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-9M2jmE-JKqE/TrxvEQRMFJI/AAAAAAAAAFA/3imu9FDUyLo/s200/mo_after.jpg" width="150" /></a></td></tr><tr><td class="tr-caption" style="text-align: center;">Angry face - Day 0!</td></tr></tbody></table>Movember aims to raise support and awareness for mens' health issues, particularly depression and prostate cancer. Both of these issues aren't seen as "manly" things to talk about, so I think the association with facial hair (seriously, how hard do you have to work to make a beard/moustache unmanly) is a good way of breaking the ice.</div><div style="text-align: justify;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: justify;">I haven't yet decided what style I'll end up with by November 30 - any suggestions? And if you'd like to get on board and support me, you can do so over at my <a href="http://mobro.co/andrewdotnich">"MoSpace" page</a> :D</div><br /><br /><br /></div>

]]></content>
